1000 Virtues of Imam Ali a.s. App Privacy Policy (Android)
This privacy policy governs your use of the application: 1000 Virtues of Imam Ali a.s. for Android.
User Provided Information
When you open the app we ask you multiple information:
Your preference of Language.
As we provide this App in multiple languages.
Whether you want to receive notifications.
Whether you want to share this app on your facebook profile.
Other information related to above items. That includes, but not limited to, your preferred selection, date and time of selection.
We store this information in your device so that App can retain the options you selected.
We might deliver this information to our server to retain the data and analyze it to provide better service to our users.
Automatically Collected Information
In addition, to provide you with better usability and for our statistics, the application may collect certain information automatically, including, but not limited to: Android Advertising Identifier, the type of Mobile Device you use, your Mobile Device Unique ID, the IP Address of your Mobile Device, your Mobile Operating System, the type of Mobile Internet Browser you use, and information about the way you use the application.
We might deliver this information to our server to retain the data and analyze it to provide better service to our users.
Does the Application collect precise real time location information of the device?
No, we do not use any tracking of real time location of your device.
Does the Application uses Camera/Photo-Gallery of the device?
No, we do not use Camera/Photo Gallery of your device.
Does the Application uses Push Notifications?
You have the option to enable it and if you do not enable it then you will not receive notifications. If you enable notifications then the App delivers your Device Unique Id, Device Model, and a Random Token that allow us to deliver notifications precisely to your device.
We might also store this information in our server so that we can deliver you notifications from our server.
Do third parties see and/or have access to information obtained by the Application?
In general cases we don't share the information. But in specific situations we will share your information with third parties only in the ways that are described in this privacy statement:
As required by law, such as to comply with a subpoena, or similar legal process;
When we believe in good faith that disclosure is necessary to protect our rights, protect your safety or the safety of others, investigate fraud, or respond to a government request;
If this App is involved in a merger, acquisition, or sale of all or a portion of its assets
Apart from above information we use third party services in our App that can track your usage and identity that includes, but not limited to, Android Advertising Identifier, your Device Model, your IP Address, your Mobile Operation System.
Below are the services embedded in our App and we advise you to read their privacy policies:
Google Play Servcies
Facebook
What are my opt-out rights?
You can stop all collection of information by the application easily by uninstalling the application.
Children
We do not use the application to knowingly solicit data from or market to children under the age of 13. If a parent or guardian becomes aware that his or her child has provided us with information without their consent, he or she should contact us at ghulamekambar@gmail.com. We will delete such information from our files within a reasonable time.
Changes
This Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time for any reason. We will notify you of any changes to our Privacy Policy by posting the new Privacy Policy
here
. You are advised to consult this Privacy Policy regularly for any changes, as continued use is deemed approval of all changes.
Your Consent
By using the application, you are consenting to our processing of your information as set forth in this Privacy Policy now and as amended by us.
Contact us
If you believe that any information we are holding on you is incorrect or incomplete, please email us as soon as possible at the following address. We will promptly correct any information found to be incorrect.
